\item Step 4.  Computing the Test Statistic.

The test statistic is computed by the following equation:

\begin{align*}
t_{obtained} &= r \sqrt{ \frac{n - 2}{1 - r^2}} \\
              &= 0.721 \sqrt{ \frac{20 - 2}{1 - 0.721^2}} \\
              &= 4.4145 \\
\end{align*}

From table(12.2, SPSS printout), we find Pearson Correlation coefficient, $r = 0.721$.  Using the above equation, the test statistic is 4.41.

